          "solution_type": "detailed",
          "content_html": "<p>The CH<sub>3</sub> carbon is <i>sp</i><sup>3</sup>; the double-bond carbons are <i>sp</i><sup>2</sup>; the C<span data-math=\"\\text{=}\"></span>C−C and C<span data-math=\"\\text{=}\"></span>C−H bond angles are approximately 120°; other bond angles are near 109°.</p>\n<img src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBb2tVIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--f1a5688dd803439fa16f140b6d2f073c49d80018/OChem_01_EC_206.jpg\" alt=\"The chemical structure of propene featuring the wedge-dash bonds between hydrogen and C3.\">"
